Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.36,0:04:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Great hat. Great hat.\N>> Merry Christmas. Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.95,0:04:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.\NGloria in excelsius the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.19,0:04:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,praise be to thee oh Lord\Nmost high
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.68,0:05:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in whose name we are assembled today.\NThe 91st Psalm says that those who put
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.36,0:05:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,their faith in me are mine.\NKrishna says
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.75,0:05:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,those who believe in me\Nare mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.84,0:05:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. We need to make an couple of\Nannouncements and we'll start.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.75,0:05:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> God said we need to make a couple of\Nannouncements.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.03,0:06:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\NThere's much literature about the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.68,0:06:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,obligation of the student to the\Nteacher. I turn it around the other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.19,0:06:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm concerned about the obligation and\Nthe promise and responsibility of the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.08,0:06:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,teacher to the student.\NI'm answerable for all of you. So keep
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that in mind.\NYou screw up, I'm in trouble. You know
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.68,0:06:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what I mean?\NYes, we'll get to we have a slide on the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.52,0:06:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,obligation of the spiritual teacher to\Nbe straightforward, honest, to try to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.88,0:06:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,remain as simple as possible and to be\Ncompletely transparent,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.56,0:07:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,needs nothing, wants nothing from\Nstudents, has nothing to do with their
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.19,0:07:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,personal lives, doesn't try to control\Nthem, doesn't tell them what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.91,0:07:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,has freedom to come and go. Don't have\Nto sign up for anything. No obligations,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.00,0:07:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,no oaths.\NThat's a cheerful start, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.19,0:07:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we're going to go through, as\Nyou know, we have uh by now over a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.52,0:07:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,hundred slides\Nfrom various lectures. So, what we're
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.47,0:07:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,going to do, how many people here are\Nnew? How many people are new?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.36,0:07:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo, I'm going to emphasize the basics
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.56,0:07:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,then. The basics and the the charts that\Nare farther along in the lecture series
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.24,0:07:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,uh are in the books. You know, the uh\Ncalibration of the most famous
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.19,0:08:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,scientists in history etc. uh those are\Nall very interesting. But today I really
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.12,0:08:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,want to cover the basics and reemphasize\Nthen
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.00,0:08:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,um a few concepts and once you they\Nincorporate them the the rest of them
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.68,0:08:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,become much easier. A couple of very\Nbasic premises.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.28,0:08:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Um I speak from several different uh\Nexperiential backgrounds simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.68,0:08:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know I practice psychiatry,\Npsychalysis, psychology etc. for 50
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.15,0:08:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,years. had a huge practice.\NI also had what the world calls rather
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.08,0:08:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,unusual spiritual experiences starting\Nvery young age three and very intense
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.72,0:08:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout my life that transformed uh\Nthe inner context of existence and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.60,0:08:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,reality.\NTherefore, I I saw some things
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.12,0:09:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,differently than other people and some\Nthings I thought were quite useful
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.88,0:09:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're incorporated into the\Nlecture series as consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.56,0:09:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,research. So, we'll also be talking\Nabout spiritual reality and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.20,0:09:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness\Nuh research.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.12,0:09:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason for that is mankind has never\Nhad the capacity to tell truth from
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.16,0:09:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood.\NHere
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.36,0:09:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we wander around this planet\Nfor zillions of years and you can't even
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.76,0:09:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,tell truth from falsehood\Nletting a kid loose on the desert with
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.00,0:09:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,no compass. Good luck.\NHow we even survived where we are today
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.95,0:09:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is amazing to me.\NYou know, man has been at war 93% of the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.80,0:09:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,time. 93% of the time. It's been\Ncontinuous since I've been born.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.27,0:10:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born after World War I. And it's\Nbeen one war after another ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.27,0:10:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The 7% of time man wasn't at war. He's\Nprobably too sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.39,0:10:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The plague or some great catastrophe\Nuh kept him from his usual business.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.83,0:10:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll we'll discover why that is. Why\Nis man so warlike?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.07,0:10:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He talks peace, but it's the last thing\Nhe wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.80,0:10:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Man talks peace, but it's the last thing\Nhe wants. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.44,0:10:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Got that?\NHe talks peace, but he doesn't want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.68,0:10:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a threat of peace.\NCrashes the stock market and everything
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.27,0:10:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,else, right?\NMan talks peace, but he lives by war.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.60,0:11:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll see why that is because we'll\Ncover that when we when we discuss the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.72,0:11:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of the ego over evolutionary\Ntime. And we'll see what the impact of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.24,0:11:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that is on man's brain physiology.\NSpiritual intention and alignment
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.83,0:11:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,absolutely alters your brain physiology\Nso that you see things and process them
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.60,0:11:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,differently, understand them\Ndifferently.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.39,0:11:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,At the present time, you know, on the\Ncalibrated level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.56,0:11:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,uh truth starts at 200 and goes up to a\Nthousand. That which is not true is 200
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.60,0:11:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and below.\N85% of mankind calibrates below 200 at
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.36,0:11:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the present time.\NThat should give you more realistic
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.04,0:11:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,expectations of earthly life.\NSo now we have uh slides. We'll start
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.44,0:12:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,with one we all start with. And uh yes.\NNow what? Do you see the same thing on
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.36,0:12:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,all three screens?\N>> No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.44,0:12:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,>> No.\N>> I thought maybe I'd have to run back and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.27,0:12:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,forth between the screens.\NThat's a lucky break.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.39,0:12:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I didn't need my kid my gym shoes after\Nall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.20,0:12:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWell, we'll talk about how this came to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.48,0:12:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,be came to be. Uh I was uh as I said I\Nhad a very large clinic and we got we
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.51,0:12:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,had the most hopeless patients from all\Nover the world. They flew them in from
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.27,0:12:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,all over the world and uh thousand we\Nhad thousand new patients a year
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.63,0:12:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely hopeless\Nand therefore uh I used every modality
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.04,0:12:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that could possibly help people.\NAcupuncture, nutrition, everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.63,0:12:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And each thing that we added made a\Ndifference.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.63,0:13:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You would take uh 10 hopeless cases and\Nput them on certain kinds of diets.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.68,0:13:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven of them would cure. That left\Nseven to go. Those seven we would test
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.48,0:13:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,them for cerebral allergy. Four of them\Nwould we would find what it is. Four
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.63,0:13:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,would go. You only got three left.\NAnd we used kinesiology which I learned
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.12,0:13:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from Diamond Dr. Diamond.\NUh so
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.88,0:13:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I was giving a lecture one time on\Nkinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.20,0:13:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology is so simple that if you\Ncan't understand it, you have to leave
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.76,0:13:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,this audience immediately.\NI need your This is Susan. My right arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.80,0:13:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,who has done many thousands of\Ncalibrations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.16,0:14:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She's very quick and fast. That's why I\Nuse her all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.19,0:14:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She's also inexpensive. She\N>> I don't charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.39,0:14:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, I was teaching kinesiology things\Nthat I'd learned with George Diamond and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.56,0:14:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was teaching it to our staff.\NAnd the first thing we one of the first
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.36,0:14:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,things that we demonstrated was if you\Ntake uh naive subjects and have them
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.12,0:14:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,look at look at fluorescent lights\Nthey'll go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.92,0:14:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now she's not a naive subject so we\Ncan't use her anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.95,0:14:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,She can't use you anymore for that. But\Nif you take just ordinary people off the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.76,0:14:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,street and we've done it with many large\Naudiences. We've done it with audiences
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.19,0:14:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of a thousand people in New York City.\NAnd uh if you take naive people and have
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.51,0:14:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,them uh hold our term and uh now I ask\Nthem ask you to resist and I push down
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.83,0:15:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with two fingers. Uh I'd say that's\Nabout 6 ounces of pressure. Wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.95,0:15:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you? Yeah. 6. And I say resist. Okay.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.56,0:15:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you take naive people and have\Nthem look at the fluorescent light, I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.51,0:15:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,put your arm up. I'm g I'm going to hold\Nsomething in mind. Okay. What I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.44,0:15:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,holding in mind calibrates over 200\Nresist. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.19,0:15:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a person look at fluorescent\Nlights, their arm will go weak. If you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.88,0:15:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,hold pesticides over the solar plexus,\Ntheir arm will go weak. Sweet and low.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.68,0:15:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We used to pass it out to the audience\Nand and uh count count in twos. One's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.39,0:15:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the doctor, one's the patient.\NAnyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.39,0:15:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,certain things made everybody go weak.\NFluorescent lights especially. Think of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.92,0:15:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,all the people working all day, all\Ntheir lives under fluorescent lights
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.04,0:15:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that are making their energies go weak\Nall day long. Yeah. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.75,0:16:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I was demonstrating it. So that night at\Nthe clinic I said uh you can sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.68,0:16:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. I said I need some\Nvolunteers. So some people volunteered.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.48,0:16:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh we had an attitudinal healing center.\NJerry Jolsky came over and he started
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.75,0:16:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the first one on Tibon and we had the\Nsecond one. Uh so I said I need some
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.44,0:16:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,students\Nuh to teach a class in kinesiology and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.00,0:16:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nthey they were doing the course of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.04,0:16:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,miracles and uh so I said okay kid look\Nlook at the fluorescent lights and they
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.07,0:16:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,did not go weak said what look at the\Nlights and I read they did not go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.32,0:16:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,they did not go weak with pesticides or\Nsweet and low
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.04,0:16:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,something had happened something was\Ndifferent about these people who were
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.24,0:16:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual students\NSo I started a research small research
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.00,0:16:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,project. Uh a number of people just\Nstarting the course of miracles and I
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.27,0:17:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,tested them out at the very beginning of\Nthe course before they started. They all
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.95,0:17:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,went weak with pesticides. They all went\Nweak with fluorescent lights and we
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.91,0:17:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,retested them about once a week and by\Nthe time they got to lesson 75 around in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.95,0:17:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,there 75 85\Nall of a sudden they would not go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.43,0:17:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to anything.\NSomething had happened to their
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.48,0:17:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness that made them immune to\Nthe adverse effects of negative stimuli.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.40,0:17:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They were no longer subject to what was\Nout there. And that was the premise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.52,0:17:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You're only subject to what you hold in\Nmind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.84,0:17:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It progressed from there then that I\Ndiscovered a scale of consciousness of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.40,0:17:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,one to a thousand. And on the scale of\Nconsciousness using the same technique
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.96,0:17:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we just uh uh did uh we calibrated all\Nthe major emotions
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.32,0:17:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,uh we had have a scale that goes from 1\Nto a,000 of logarithmic scale these
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.20,0:18:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,numbers are 10. So this is 10 * 10 150\Ntimes. This is 10 * 10 259 50 times
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.52,0:18:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,which is exponential\Nlogarithmic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.16,0:18:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is it logarithmic or exponential?\NAnybody know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.03,0:18:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It's logarithmic exponential.\NIt covers it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.28,0:18:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The the highest possible\Ncalibration in this planet earthly human
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.08,0:18:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,life is a thousand.\NYeah. Because that's the way we set up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.60,0:18:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the scale. The lowest is death at at\None. You know, life begins at one and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.96,0:18:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,goes up to 1,000. We found that anything\Nand everything in this planet could be
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.36,0:18:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated. And what we discovered we\Nwere discovering is how to tell
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.12,0:18:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,perception from essence. How to tell\Nreality from appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.67,0:19:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Decart accord the great philosopher.\NThe difference between what a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.16,0:19:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,looks like and what it actually is.\NThe wolf in sheep's clothing. How do you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.91,0:19:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,discern it? And of course, Socrates, my\Nfavorite philosopher, said, "All men
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.16,0:19:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,chooses only the good." That helps you\Nput in place the Christian
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.03,0:19:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,premise of forgiveness. How can you\Nforgive people that seem so? When you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.55,0:19:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,recall Socrates teaching, all men choose\Nwhat they think and believe to be the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.67,0:19:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,good. The only problem is they cannot\Ndiscern the real good from the false
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.00,0:19:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,good. Therefore the basic problem is\Nagain ignorance not knowing essence from
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.67,0:19:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance.\NSo what we had discovered then with the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.16,0:19:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated levels of consciousness is\Nhow to discern essence from appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.20,0:19:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time in human history,\Nman goes by appearance and opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.32,0:20:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So using the same simple arm\Ntechnique uh to hold the thing in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.91,0:20:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we calibrate something\Num I'll just calibrate something. You
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.88,0:20:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to uh I'm holding something\Nin mind now. I'm holding something in
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.12,0:20:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,mind. I want you to resist. Resist.\NOkay. I'm holding something else in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.00,0:20:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,now. I want you to resist.\NThe first thing I was holding in mind is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.76,0:20:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a fake\Num a fake uh
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.20,0:20:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,huh a fake Picasso. Yeah, fake Picasso.\NI just was holding a picture of that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.32,0:20:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,fake Picasso at home. And then I also\Nhave a couple of legitimate dollies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.76,0:20:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Dollies. Yeah. And I have another\Npainting. Let's see if this is a true a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.55,0:20:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,real one too. I'm holding this one in\Nmine. resist. Thank God that's a miro.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.67,0:21:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a MO lithograph.\NMaro died at age 90 and it suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.88,0:21:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,became very valuable. So anyway, I keep\Nit out in the garage so that no harm
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.72,0:21:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,going to.\NSo there's objections to kinesiology and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.28,0:21:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the problem of the people who\Nmake the objections because you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.48,0:21:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,uh even a child can do this and we did a\Nvideo I think it's called power versus
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.12,0:21:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,force in which we just use a simple\Nchild and uh so
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.20,0:21:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it it's very simplistic\Nas you can see it's not suggestive
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.67,0:21:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because she doesn't know what I'm\Nholding in mind. The trouble that people
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.60,0:21:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,ask me tonight's about dowsing. If\Nyou're some super experts are can do it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.08,0:21:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,with dowsing. The trouble with dowsing\Nis the subject and the answer are both
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.55,0:21:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the same person. The questioner and the\Nanswer are the same person. And one
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.36,0:21:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,could have a prejudice in one way or the\Nother that might influence the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.15,0:22:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So if it's something really critical, I\Ndon't tell her what I'm holding in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.48,0:22:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because I don't want the slightest\Nchance of any kind of suggestion taking
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.76,0:22:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,place.\NTo be able to do it, you have to be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.15,0:22:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,dedicated to truth, not to uh seeking\Nreinforcement of your favorite
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.08,0:22:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,positionality.\NYou understand? Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.60,0:22:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's like a compass. The compass then\Nman was without a compass. He couldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.64,0:22:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,tell the truth from falsehood. Now he\Nhas a compass that's calibrated all the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.79,0:22:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,way to a th00and.\NAnd uh so we found that everything below
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.12,0:22:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,level 200 was false.\NEverything above 200 was true. And we I
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.96,0:22:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,then incorporated from psychoanalysis\Nalso the perennial wisdom
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.76,0:22:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,uh also the great chain of being a very\Nso this is a very familiar
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.12,0:23:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh listing of levels of consciousness\Nwith shame and disgrace and guilt and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.28,0:23:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,apathy all the negative ones down here.\NColumbia psychoanalytic.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.72,0:23:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Shandor taught adaptational\Npsychonamics, a variation of fraudian
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.67,0:23:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,psychoanalysis.\NThese recall the emergency emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.24,0:23:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,These recall the welfare emotions. Yeah.\NSo it also correlates with
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.48,0:23:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,psychoanalysis.\NI spent four years of psychoanalysis
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.32,0:23:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with Lionel Overy who was a professor at\NColumbia University whose analyst was
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.20,0:23:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Abraham Cardner whose analyst was Freud.\NSo Freud's my great-grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.32,0:23:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He was an atheist.\NMy first analyst and I were both
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.28,0:23:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,atheists. We agreed that it was all\Nnonsensical
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.72,0:23:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh\Nthat lasts you a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.60,0:24:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then uh so here we have all the the\Nbasic feelings and of course we wrote a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.15,0:24:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,book called transcending the levels of\Nconsciousness in which we look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.12,0:24:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,upside and the downside of what is\Nholding each one of these levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.91,0:24:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What's holding all negative things in in\Nplace is one single thing. You don't
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.36,0:24:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,have to give up anything in this whole\Nworld
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.60,0:24:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to get off these things here. All you\Nhave to give up is one thing repeatedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.44,0:24:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing. No matter what the one thing\Nis. Hating your mother-in-law, feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.40,0:24:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,guilty about something, being overcome\Nwith greed and lust or what. The only
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.24,0:24:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,thing you got to give up is the juice\Nthat you're getting out of it. The
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.08,0:24:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,secret pleasure that you're getting out\Nof it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.52,0:24:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are people so addicted to hatred?\NBecause they get such wonderful juice
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.48,0:24:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,out of it. It's just so wonderful to get\Nout there and have a parade and pick it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.24,0:25:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and riot and\Nhave a whole hate orgy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.20,0:25:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You watch them on TV, they've got that\Nglee of or there's like an orgy look.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.84,0:25:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you get that look, you can see it\Nall over the world of whatever the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.88,0:25:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,parade is, whatever the issue is, it's\Nall the same look. I'm right and you're
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.40,0:25:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong. Yeah. So,\Nso to get off anything then you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.44,0:25:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,just be willing to give up whatever\Njuice you're getting off of it. You say,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.40,0:25:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, I'm not getting any juice out of\Nsuffering." Oh, yes, you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.24,0:25:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're getting lots and lots of juice. I\Nknow people that are still suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.15,0:25:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,over loss of a family member 30 years\Nago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.00,0:25:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it time to get over it?\NNo, it's become a lifestyle. Lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.96,0:25:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and the indictiveness that goes with it.\NSee it every night on television.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.48,0:25:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get over it. What was the\Neagle? The Eagles had a song. Let's get
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.76,0:26:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,over it. Wasn't that the name of it?\NIt's time to get over it. That getting
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.96,0:26:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,over it merely comes from being willing\Nto let go the energy that we get out of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.55,0:26:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the the negative positionality.\NWe finally get up to a level called
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.36,0:26:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,courage. Level courage.\NCourage is the willingness to tell the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.64,0:26:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,truth. It's the f first step in all the\N12step step groups. It's the willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.00,0:26:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to take responsibility and be honest.\NThen you move up to neutrality. Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.08,0:26:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,neutrality is a very comfortable place\Nto be. Uh neutrality if you get the job
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.36,0:26:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it's fine and if you don't you'll find\Nanother. So what's the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.08,0:26:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We need lots more people and neutrality\Nin the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.64,0:26:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,People worry about the world ending in\Nthe year 2012. What's the next time the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.40,0:26:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,world supposed to be in the Mayan\Ncalendar? Let's take care of the Mayan
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.15,0:26:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,calendar.\NThe world is going to end in 2012.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.52,0:27:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NFolks, it's not going to end in 2012.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.36,0:27:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you who are counting on it, I\Nhate to disappoint you. The Mayan
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.84,0:27:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,calendar has been wrong for thousands of\Nyears and it's going to be wrong for
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.20,0:27:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of years. Why is that? Because\Nyou can't predict the future. The future
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.60,0:27:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is not set. If this future was set,\Nthere would be no personal
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.79,0:27:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,responsibility, no karmic\Nresponsibility. There would really be no
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.55,0:27:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,point to evolution itself because this\Nworld is optimal for spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.27,0:27:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution. This world gives you the opp\Noptimum opportunity to gain positive
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.12,0:27:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,karma and undo negative karma.\NTherefore, this world is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.40,0:28:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a perfect world. Resist Zoe.\NThat's the essence and appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.52,0:28:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If God wanted a place where your spirit\Ncould evolve, he he would create earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.32,0:28:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't he? Where you every moment you\Nhave to make a choice. Every single
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.84,0:28:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,moment you have to make a choice. You\Ndon't have any choice not to make a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.72,0:28:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,choice. You always have to make a\Nchoice. Constantly. So
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.27,0:28:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the spirit is like a little electromag\Nlittle uh iron filing in the infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.36,0:28:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,field of consciousness which is the\Nlight of God out of which arose
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.60,0:28:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,creation.\NTherefore every choice and every
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.08,0:28:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,decision you make alters the\Nenergy of this little iron filing that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.03,0:28:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is within this giant electromagnetic\Nfield.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.55,0:28:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, everything comes about as a\Nconsequence of karmic choice. Every time
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.67,0:28:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you make a positive choice, this\Npolarity increases. A negative choice, a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.55,0:29:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,negative flarity.\NTherefore, where you are in the overall
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.48,0:29:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,field is automatically the consequence\Nof that which you are. That's which you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.24,0:29:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are is determining what is.\NThere's no point to worry about judgment
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.00,0:29:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,day because it's happened.\NToday is judgment day. Resist. Today and
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.60,0:29:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,every day is judgment day. There's no\Npoint about worrying about some horrible
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.48,0:29:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,god in the future who's going to beat\Nyou up, throw you into hell cuz he hits
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.20,0:29:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you.\NYou've done it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.36,0:29:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So that the justice of God is\Nabsolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.76,0:29:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because it is based on the reality\Nof that which you have chosen of your
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.08,0:29:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,own free choice. And God's will for us\Nis free choice. Free choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.36,0:30:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To say such things makes me in in the\Neyes of a relativist, an absolutist.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.24,0:30:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I might as well warn everybody here. I\Nam an absolutist.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.36,0:30:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the absolutism of absolutism that\Nmakes it so absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.60,0:30:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You chop off a finger, folks. It's not\Nrelative, it's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.91,0:30:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I always get a kick out of relativist\Nwhen it comes to money. You know, these
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.15,0:30:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,crazy professors and all they ridicule\Neverything, every kind of reality, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.52,0:30:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But when it comes to money, it's amazing\Nhow what an absolutist they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.67,0:30:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,One man's 50 is another man's 20. Uh-uh.\NThat does not go. One man's 50 is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.67,0:30:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody's 50. Every one of these\Nrelativists is an absolutist when it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.72,0:31:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,comes down to the reality of everyday\Nlife. It's a nice game game to play
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.84,0:31:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,politically, philosophically.\NAll right. So neutrality, willingness in
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.84,0:31:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the 300s are very powerful.\NThe 300s are very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.48,0:31:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh they build uh great and do wonderful\Nhumanitarian beneficial things. Rick
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.91,0:31:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Warren is what he writes is up there in\Nthe high 350s.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.32,0:31:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You get up to the level of 400s, you're\Ntalking about the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.12,0:31:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,non-emotional, non-emotional reason and\Nlogic. And then at the great scientific
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.84,0:31:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,geniuses uh Einstein and uh\NFreud etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.88,0:31:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,are at calibration level 499.\N499 is as far as you can go with reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.76,0:32:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You the intellect you can prove what is.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.48,0:32:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the differential calculus 499.\NAll right. So the reason and the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.20,0:32:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,intellect then is in the mid range of\Nthe mid 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.08,0:32:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're still talking about linear\Nreality. Linear
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.36,0:32:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that means content.\NNow when you get to level 500, you bring
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.24,0:32:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in context. Context because now you're\Nmoving to the nonlinear love. At 500 is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.67,0:32:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the emergence of the nonlinear.\NSo from 500 up then we have love and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.96,0:32:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,then we move on into the higher levels\Nof selfless love. Selfless love.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.08,0:32:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh the 12 step groups alcohol anonymous\Ncalibrates at 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.36,0:32:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,540.\NThat's the top few percentage of all of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.84,0:33:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind. 540. Only 4% of mankind ever\Ngets beyond level 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.72,0:33:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,0.4 4 gets to 540.\NPeople who have recovered in 12step
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.00,0:33:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,programs or course of miracles etc\Nbelong to 0.4%
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.67,0:33:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world's population statistically.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.72,0:33:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so 540 gives you is the beginning of a\Ntransformation and it comes about via
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.79,0:33:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,illumination.\NAs you get towards level 600, they have
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.91,0:33:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to f about at about 570\Nis uh saintthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.84,0:33:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh the Dalai Lama, the Pope, uh Father\NPeio, the level of 570 is is saintthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.91,0:33:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And from 540 and up and especially\Naround 570,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.24,0:33:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,there emerges the miraculous.\Nthe miraculous about which mankind goes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.08,0:34:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in and awe. But in experiential reality,\Nthe miraculous
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.08,0:34:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is nothing but the unfolding of a\Nnatural phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.56,0:34:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,When you realize that evolution and\Ncreation are one and the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.24,0:34:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,right now there's so much controversy\Nabout intelligent design versus
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.20,0:34:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,creationism,\Netc.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.44,0:34:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That which shines forth\Nin the description of Genesis,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.56,0:34:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the light of God shone forth out of\Nwhich arose all of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.96,0:34:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing that arose was the energy\Nfield of life itself. And so everything
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.00,0:34:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that we calibrate is in comparison to an\Ninfinite field of consciousness. The
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.83,0:34:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite field called consciousness\Nwhich is beyond time and place beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.35,0:35:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,time and place has no beginning and no\Nending.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.16,0:35:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's impossible to prove the\Nexistence of God because that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.44,0:35:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite, limitless, has no beginning\Nand ending is in a different paradigm of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.72,0:35:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,reality than proof. Proof is the world\Nof the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.76,0:35:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual reality starts at 500 and up.\NIt has to do with essence. It has to do
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.59,0:35:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,with radical subjectivity.\NThe reason certain things became
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.28,0:35:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,apparent apparent was because when I saw\Nkinesiology demonstrated,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.16,0:35:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,they presumed that it was a local\Nphenomena based on the Newtonian premise
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.88,0:35:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of causality. Causality applies to the\Nenergy fuels of the 400 science.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.48,0:35:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But the way things come about is not via\Ncausality. That is a mentalization that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.68,0:36:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you project into the world like you do\Nwith time. There is no time out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.64,0:36:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no space. There's no distance.\NThere's no causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.80,0:36:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's no before or after.\NThat's the way it looks to your
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.24,0:36:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,witnessing. The fact that you witness\Nthings progressively doesn't mean that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.00,0:36:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,they are that way in the universe. You\Nsee the grandiosity of the ego. If I see
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.88,0:36:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it that way, that's the way it must be\Nin the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.48,0:36:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The universe has no interest in in in\Nthe sequence in which you're witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.20,0:36:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,events.\NSo what you're actually watching is that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.59,0:36:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is occurring of its own\Nspontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.11,0:36:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as an as the phenomenon of emergence\Npotentiality becoming an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.72,0:36:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Things do not happen by causality as an\Nimpossibility because you end up in an
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.07,0:37:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite progressive\Nseries. You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.80,0:37:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that happens is happening\Nspontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.83,0:37:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't even any personal you making\Nit happen. Although you think there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.48,0:37:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Duality arises from thinking that there\Nis a separate personal you that is the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.04,0:37:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,originator\Nof all action, the motivator, the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.92,0:37:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,decider.\NIn reality, everything is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.32,0:37:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneously.\NPotential potentiality when local
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.40,0:37:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions are right emerges into an\Nactuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.00,0:37:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the same phenomena we see\Nwithin the miraculous. The miraculous is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.72,0:37:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing but potentiation,\Nthe activation of that potentiation into
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.32,0:37:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,an actuality\Nby virtue of the field of the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.59,0:37:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The higher the spiritual energy of the\Ncontext, the greater the likelihood that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.24,0:38:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what is held in mind will potentiate.\NAt a certain level of consciousness, the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.24,0:38:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,witnessing of life is once one\Ncontinuous miracle after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.83,0:38:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening of its own by\Nvirtue of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.59,0:38:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know what all that meant, but\Nit certainly sounded good, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.76,0:38:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what it means.\NMeans we should go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.64,0:38:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In this in this this lifetime, the\Nreason I recognized what what's going on
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.20,0:38:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,with kinesiology is because I'd had\Nrather astonishing spiritual experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.59,0:38:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout life, starting at a very\Nyoung age. People like me to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.64,0:39:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it, so I gave it a few minutes. The rest\Nof it's in the book. It began at age
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.04,0:39:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,three when out of nothingness\Nthere came the sudden shock of existence
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.35,0:39:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,out of oblivion\Nout of the void
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.68,0:39:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,where I went from previous lifetimes\Nand the hinyana Buddhist is into the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.68,0:39:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,void. I would leave that lifetime in the\Nvoid. this lifetime at age three
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.40,0:39:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly there was a shock was like\Nsuddenly somebody turned on the cle
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.80,0:39:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,lights and I realized that I existed.\NIt was a stunning terrible shock. I was
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.40,0:39:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,not happy about it.\NI was not pleased to exist. Not only was
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.28,0:39:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it bad enough to exist, but with it went\Nthis little body,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.96,0:39:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,three-year-old body in a wagon. First\Nyou exist. Secondly, you got this body
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.44,0:39:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with you. Oh my god. The next thing that\Narose, this is all nonverbal. The next
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.11,0:40:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,thing that arose was suddenly the fear\Nof non-existence. If I had come had come
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.68,0:40:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,into existence, then it could have\Narisen that I would not have come in
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.44,0:40:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,come into existence\Nwhich was just a total awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.48,0:40:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The so there arose the conundrum which\Nuh this life was about for many years
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.04,0:40:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,was reality existence or non-existence\Nwas reality beyond existence or
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.16,0:40:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,non-existence\Nuh which can't be solved you go past
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.80,0:40:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level 850 so I came in as\Nnothingness nothingness was the absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.59,0:40:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,reality nothingness\Nfrom there a lot of um rather profound
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.52,0:40:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,own spiritual experiences happened. They\Nwere all spontaneous
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.76,0:40:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in which um I experienced the infinite\Nradiance of the self and um
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.16,0:41:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,whether the physical body continued to\Nexist or not was totally irrelevant
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.92,0:41:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because in that state it's timeless. So\Nin a snowbank somewhere in the highways
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.40,0:41:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of Wisconsin,\NI climbed in out of this blizzard
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.83,0:41:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and this incredible blissful condition\Nover overwhelmed and there was no
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.92,0:41:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,personal self anymore. Just an infinite\Npresence
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.56,0:41:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all description beyond all time\Nwith no beginning and no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.80,0:41:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's\Nits characteristics were power power
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.00,0:41:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all description. The power of\Ndivine love is invincible.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.88,0:41:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Its invincibility is based on the fact\Nthat it is absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.72,0:41:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The absolute power of divinity is an\Nabsolute
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.56,0:42:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nsimultaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.83,0:42:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,exquisitly soft\Nso that what was left of the self
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.11,0:42:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,personal self melts melted into this\Ninfinite beingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.52,0:42:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then came the knowingness, the reality\Nthat that which I am existed before all
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.40,0:42:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,time.\NThat which I am will exist beyond all
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.24,0:42:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,universes after all universes have\Ndisappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.68,0:42:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist\Nan absolute knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.68,0:42:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing about spirituality\Nis that it is an absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.00,0:42:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,experientially experientially it is an\Nabsolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.64,0:42:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nonverbal. No questions can be\Nasked none arise because they have all
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.07,0:42:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,been answered.\NBecause of such experiences when I saw
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.44,0:43:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology I saw that it was not a\NNewtonian causal cause and effect kind
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.56,0:43:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of relationship. What I saw was that\Nwhat the person was responding to was
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.24,0:43:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of consciousness\Nitself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.40,0:43:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a linear causality.\NWhen I hold in mind something and press
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.72,0:43:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,down her arm,\NI'm holding the energy field of the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.11,0:43:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,essence of that.\NAnd what her arm is responding to is the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.07,0:43:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,essence. If the evidence is over 200,\Nshe says strong. If the essence is under
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.76,0:43:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,200, she goes weak. She doesn't even\Nknow why I'm holding in mind. Everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.96,0:43:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,got that?\NI'm going to get that very well settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.83,0:43:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nonlinear. It has nothing to do\Nwith reason, argument, logic, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.24,0:43:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Right? So all comes about then as a\Nvirtue of that which it is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.64,0:44:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality\Nwhich is actualized by the field. So the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.31,0:44:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,field is what actualizes the\Nkinesiologic response. It's also the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.68,0:44:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,field that actualizes what the world\Ncalls the miraculous from energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.83,0:44:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,540.\NThe miraculous is common in 12step
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.24,0:44:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,groups and course of miracles of course\Nis based on that 570 and up. Uh the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.31,0:44:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,miraculous is almost continuous.\NEverything is just in place the way it's
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.31,0:44:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,supposed to be and everything is\Nperfect. And so the world go doesn't go
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.28,0:44:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,from imperfection to perfection.\NThe world in reality when you really see
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.40,0:44:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it for what it is goes from perfection\Nto perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.11,0:44:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,As a spiritual discipline, then you make\Na decision to see the intrinsic beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.64,0:45:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and perfection of all that exists. No\Nmatter what,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.64,0:45:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind will make objections. You don't\Nmean that garbage can over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.24,0:45:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I mean that garbage can over there.\NI remember walking down an alley in New
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.88,0:45:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,York City and here's two old be garbage\Ncans and a couple of mice running around
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.64,0:45:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and I I merged into that awareness. It\Nwas like an incredible incredible
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.83,0:45:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,painting. It was like an impressionistic\Npainting. Here's these garbage cans like
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.48,0:45:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,this and little mice like this running\Nall over and everything is all collapsed
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.24,0:45:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,like that and the tin can iss laying\Nthere and it's just a stunning
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.96,0:45:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you call it montage or whatever\Nthe word is in in art
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.44,0:45:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with every within everything that is\Nbecause of its perfection. Everything
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.40,0:45:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,goes from perfection to perfection. You\Nsay, "Well, what about this halfrown
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.76,0:46:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,rose? Is it an imperfect rose?" No, it's\Na perfectly halfgrown rose. You
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.07,0:46:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,understand? A thing can only move from\Nperfection to perfection. This is a
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.11,0:46:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect perfect half-grown rose. This is\Na perfect 3/4. This is a perfect full.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.40,0:46:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a perfect faded rose. This is a\Nperfect dyed dried up old nothing rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.52,0:46:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,goes from perfectly almost to perfectly\Nfull to perfectly faded to perfectly
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.92,0:46:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,dried up and then it blows away into\Nperfect dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.96,0:46:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see is perfection at every\Nsecond?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.04,0:46:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is that way.\NWhat the world what you think is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.68,0:46:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,destruction is the perfection of the\Nemergence of that potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.35,0:47:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As the ship goes over, they all drown at\Nthe same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.28,0:47:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,La.\NWasn't that a great drowning we did when
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.31,0:47:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they on the other side? Man, that really\Nturned on the TV and everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.76,0:47:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,People go out with a dramatic bang,\Ndon't they? Look at the lengths that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.59,0:47:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,people go to to get out of here. You\Nknow,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.96,0:47:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't just simply quietly slump\Nover. You got to do a whole big deal out
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.48,0:47:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of it. Drive off a cliff, have the\Npolice there. 911. God all help us. All
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.64,0:47:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,right. So, let's go.\NEverything then is the perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.07,0:47:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfillment of potential. Why? Because\Nthis world is the is perfect for the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.52,0:47:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,undoing of negative karma and the\Ngaining of positive karma. This world is
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.72,0:47:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,maximal.\NLet's see if that's so
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.68,0:48:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to ask that. That is\Nso what the Buddha said is truth. The
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.72,0:48:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha wasn't lying, folks.\NI told him, I said, "When I get back
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.52,0:48:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there, I want to remind everybody that\Nyou were telling the truth in case they
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.96,0:48:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,forgotten."\NThey think the Buddha only applies to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.04,0:48:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the Eastern world. Oh, okay. Right.\NUh,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.35,0:48:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite potentiality. Then\Nthese are the the scale of the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.28,0:48:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightened states.\NUm
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.35,0:48:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where the calibrations are.\NThey all calibrate a thousand and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.04,0:48:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Um if you ask the arm what these are,\Nthese are all like infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.59,0:48:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,uh you know well I see then then you\Nleave this uh experiential universe and
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.40,0:48:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to angels and archangels\Nand my own salvation came about in this
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.72,0:49:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetime\Nout of the pits of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.24,0:49:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I would not advise anybody to take any\Nrisk of going to hell under any
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.64,0:49:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,circumstances.\Nlet me be a witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.88,0:49:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't want to take any chances at\Nall. You just do not want to even give
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.68,0:49:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it a thought\Nto risk hell. See, because there are
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.16,0:49:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of hell far deeper than even\NDante uh realized. Dante was extremely
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.11,0:49:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,correct. the upper levels of hell\Nbecause when I hit the pits of hell
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.55,0:49:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,through inner spiritual exploration and\Nand despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.59,0:49:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I was an atheist at the time. I was a\Nreligionist uh all my life brought up in
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.59,0:49:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,a very uh religious uh environment. I\Nwas acolyte. I sang in the choir.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.11,0:50:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a boy senal sort of I sang in the\Ngreat lakes naval choir. Eventually I
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.28,0:50:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,became an atheist. The reason I how can\Nanybody so religious be an atheist. I
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.07,0:50:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,was walking through the woods one day\Nthinking of nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.40,0:50:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden\Nall the great things that have happened
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.16,0:50:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to me came as a revelation. This was not\Nsuch a great thing. This was the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.83,0:50:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,opposite. All of a sudden out of\Nnothingness out of nothingness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.92,0:50:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I grasp the totality\Nof the suffering of of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.40,0:50:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.\NThe totality of the suffering of all of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.04,0:50:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind throughout all of time.\NI was staggered. I was staggered.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.48,0:50:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In that moment, I became an atheist. I\Nsaid, "Any God that could allow
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.83,0:50:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,what I\Ncomprehended,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.64,0:51:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there couldn't be a God." And I became\Nan intense atheist, not an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.92,0:51:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to beat something, you better\Nbecome an expert at what you're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.55,0:51:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,be. And uh so I got straight A in\Ntheology, ethics,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.44,0:51:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Catholic theology, etc. So I knew what\Nmy enemy was. You know, I could ridicule
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.80,0:51:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nthe reason that prove the existence of
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.31,0:51:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,God from first cause. Give me a break.\NFirst cause still gives me a laugh.
